cwdIfChannelTable.name: cwdIfChannelTable
cwdIfChannelTable.description: This table describes the attributes of a channel group which consists of one or more downstream and upstream channels.

cwdIfChannelEntry.name: cwdIfChannelEntry
cwdIfChannelEntry.description: List of attributes for a single Channel. There is one per Point-to-multipoint card. An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of propDocsWirelessMacLayer(nnn).

cwdIfChannelUpFrequency.name: cwdIfChannelUpFrequency
cwdIfChannelUpFrequency.description: The reference center frequency used by the upstream channels in this channel.

cwdIfChannelUpWidth.name: cwdIfChannelUpWidth
cwdIfChannelUpWidth.description: The maximum bandwidth that can be used by any upstream channel. The sum of the bandwidths used by all upstream channels created within this channel cannot exceed this value.

cwdIfChannelDownFrequency.name: cwdIfChannelDownFrequency
cwdIfChannelDownFrequency.description: The reference center frequency used by the downstream channels in this channel.

cwdIfChannelDownWidth.name: cwdIfChannelDownWidth
cwdIfChannelDownWidth.description: The maximum bandwidth that can be used by any downstream channel. The sum of the bandwidths used by all downstream channels created within this channel cannot exceed this value.

cwdIfChannelMiniSlotTimeBaseTick.name: cwdIfChannelMiniSlotTimeBaseTick
cwdIfChannelMiniSlotTimeBaseTick.description: This object represents a unit of measurement of mini-slots. Upstream mini-slots and bandwidth allocations are done in multiples of this unit of time.

cwdIfChannelSubChannelPlanVer.name: cwdIfChannelSubChannelPlanVer
cwdIfChannelSubChannelPlanVer.description: This object represents the sub-channel plan version number common to both upstream and downstream supported by the hardware.

cwdIfDownstreamChannelTable.name: cwdIfDownstreamChannelTable
cwdIfDownstreamChannelTable.description: This table describes the attributes of downstream channels (frequency bands).

cwdIfDownstreamChannelEntry.name: cwdIfDownstreamChannelEntry
cwdIfDownstreamChannelEntry.description: List of attributes for a single downstream channel. The index to this table is an ifIndex with an ifType of propDocsWirelessDownStream(nnn).

cwdIfDownChannelSubChannelNumber.name: cwdIfDownChannelSubChannelNumber
cwdIfDownChannelSubChannelNumber.description: This identifies the sub-channel used by this downstream. The value of this object determines the usability of the other downstream channels.

cwdIfDownChannelId.name: cwdIfDownChannelId
cwdIfDownChannelId.description: The internal (DOCSIS) identification of the downstream channel within this particular MAC interface. If the interface is down, the object returns the last assigned value. If the downstream channel ID is unknown, this object returns a value of 0.

cwdIfDownChannelFrequency.name: cwdIfDownChannelFrequency
cwdIfDownChannelFrequency.description: The downstream center frequency associated with this channel. The channel settings determine this value.

cwdIfDownChannelWidth.name: cwdIfDownChannelWidth
cwdIfDownChannelWidth.description: The bandwidth of this downstream channel. The channel settings determine this value.

cwdIfDownChannelPower.name: cwdIfDownChannelPower
cwdIfDownChannelPower.description: At the HE, the operational transmit power. At the SU, the received power level. May be set to zero at the SU if power level measurement is not supported. If the interface is down, this object returns the configured value (if at HE), the most current value (if at SU) or zero (if not supported by the implementation).

cwdIfDownChannelModProfileIndex.name: cwdIfDownChannelModProfileIndex
cwdIfDownChannelModProfileIndex.description: An index into cwdIfModulationTable that describes modulation characteristics of this channel. This object returns 0 if the cwdIfModulationTable does not exist, or there is no corresponding row in that table that describes modulation characteristics of this channel.

cwdIfUpstreamChannelTable.name: cwdIfUpstreamChannelTable
cwdIfUpstreamChannelTable.description: Describes the attributes of attached upstream channels.

cwdIfUpstreamChannelEntry.name: cwdIfUpstreamChannelEntry
cwdIfUpstreamChannelEntry.description: List of attributes for a single upstream channel. The primary index is an ifIndex with an ifType of propDocsWirelessUpstream(nnn).

cwdIfUpChannelSubChannelNumber.name: cwdIfUpChannelSubChannelNumber
cwdIfUpChannelSubChannelNumber.description: This identifies the sub-channel used by this upstream.

cwdIfUpChannelId.name: cwdIfUpChannelId
cwdIfUpChannelId.description: The internal (DOCSIS) identification of the upstream channel within this particular MAC interface. If the interface is down, the object returns the most current value. If the upstream channel ID is unknown, this object returns a value of 0.

cwdIfUpChannelFrequency.name: cwdIfUpChannelFrequency
cwdIfUpChannelFrequency.description: The center of the upstream frequency associated with this channel. The channel settings determine this value.

cwdIfUpChannelWidth.name: cwdIfUpChannelWidth
cwdIfUpChannelWidth.description: The bandwidth of this upstream channel. The channel settings determine this value.

cwdIfUpChannelTargetPower.name: cwdIfUpChannelTargetPower
cwdIfUpChannelTargetPower.description: The target receive power of this upstream channel at the headend and the transmit power of the channel at the subscriber end.

cwdIfUpChannelModProfileIndex.name: cwdIfUpChannelModProfileIndex
cwdIfUpChannelModProfileIndex.description: An index into cwdIfModulationTable that describes modulation characteristics of this channel. This object returns 0 if the cwdIfModulationTable does not exist or is empty.

cwdIfUpChannelSlotSize.name: cwdIfUpChannelSlotSize
cwdIfUpChannelSlotSize.description: The number of units of time-slot (measured by cwdIfChannelMiniSlotTimeBaseTick) in each upstream mini-slot. Returns zero if the value is undefined or unknown.

cwdIfUpChannelTxTimingOffset.name: cwdIfUpChannelTxTimingOffset
cwdIfUpChannelTxTimingOffset.description: A measure of the current round trip time at the SU, or the maximum round trip time seen by the HE. Used for timing of SU upstream transmissions to ensure synchronized arrivals at the HE. Units are in terms of (cwdIfChannelMiniSlotTimeBaseTick/64).

cwdIfUpChannelRangBackoffStart.name: cwdIfUpChannelRangBackoffStart
cwdIfUpChannelRangBackoffStart.description: This value determines the initial contention resolution back-off window used by the SU when attempting to transmit an initial ranging request. The SU randomly selects a number within the back-off window defined by this parameter then defers this number of contention transmit opportunities before actually attempting the transmission. Expressed as a power of 2. A value of 16 at the HE indicates that a proprietary adaptive retry mechanism is to be used.

cwdIfUpChannelRangBackoffEnd.name: cwdIfUpChannelRangBackoffEnd
cwdIfUpChannelRangBackoffEnd.description: This value determines the final contention resolution back-off window used by the SU when attempting to transmit an initial ranging request. The SU randomly selects a number within the back-off window defined by this parameter then defers this number of contention transmit opportunities before actually attempting the transmission. Expressed as a power of 2. A value of 16 at the HE indicates that a proprietary adaptive retry mechanism is to be used.

cwdIfUpChannelTxBackoffStart.name: cwdIfUpChannelTxBackoffStart
cwdIfUpChannelTxBackoffStart.description: This value determines the initial contention resolution back-off window used by the SU when attempting to transmit data packets. The SU randomly selects a number within the back-off window defined by this parameter then defers this number of contention transmit opportunities before actually attempting the transmission. Expressed as a power of 2. A value of 16 at the HE indicates that a proprietary adaptive retry mechanism is to be used.

cwdIfUpChannelTxBackoffEnd.name: cwdIfUpChannelTxBackoffEnd
cwdIfUpChannelTxBackoffEnd.description: This value determines the final contention resolution back-off window used by the SU when attempting to transmit data packets. The SU randomly selects a number within the back-off window defined by this parameter then defers this number of contention transmit opportunities before actually attempting the transmission. Expressed as a power of 2. A value of 16 at the HE indicates that a proprietary adaptive retry mechanism is to be used.

cwdIfQosProfileTable.name: cwdIfQosProfileTable
cwdIfQosProfileTable.description: Describes the attributes for each class of service.

cwdIfQosProfileEntry.name: cwdIfQosProfileEntry
cwdIfQosProfileEntry.description: Describes the attributes for a single class of service. The row operation for this table is as follows: 1. This table will be implemented as read-only at the SU. SU entries are created by the agent based on information in REG-REQ MAC messages received at the SU from HE or based on information extracted from the TFTP option file 2. Creation of entries in this table is controlled by the value of cwdIfHeQosProfilePermissions. 3. There can be default entries created by the agent at the initialization time. 3. If a table is created by agent, there should only be a single entry for each Class of Service. Multiple entries with the same Class of Service parameters are not recommended as it doesn't add any extra benefit and creates extra processing of a row in the table. 4. You CAN modify a row when it is active provided you have the right cwdIfHeQosProfilePermissions. You can also change the row to notInService and change the values. An entry in this table cannot be removed while it is referenced by an entry in cwdIfSuServiceTable (Subscriber Unit) or cwdIfHeServiceTable (Head-end System). An entry in this table cannot be modified while it is referenced by an entry in cwdIfHeServiceTable. 5. If the cwdIfHeQosProfilePermissions is createBySubscriberUnits(2) then that row cannot be modified by the management system. 6. Any arbitrary integer within the range can be used as index to create a row.

cwdIfQosProfIndex.name: cwdIfQosProfIndex
cwdIfQosProfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies an entry in the cwdIfQosProfileTable. Any arbitrary integer within the range can be used as index to create a row.

cwdIfQosProfPriority.name: cwdIfQosProfPriority
cwdIfQosProfPriority.description: A relative priority assigned to this service when allocating bandwidth. Zero indicates lowest priority. seven highest. Interpretation of priority is device-specific.

cwdIfQosProfMaxUpBandwidth.name: cwdIfQosProfMaxUpBandwidth
cwdIfQosProfMaxUpBandwidth.description: The maximum upstream bandwidth, in bits per second, allowed for a service with this service class. Zero if there is no restriction of upstream bandwidth.

cwdIfQosProfGuarUpBandwidth.name: cwdIfQosProfGuarUpBandwidth
cwdIfQosProfGuarUpBandwidth.description: Minimum guaranteed upstream bandwidth, in bits per second, allowed for a service with this service class.

cwdIfQosProfMaxDownBandwidth.name: cwdIfQosProfMaxDownBandwidth
cwdIfQosProfMaxDownBandwidth.description: The maximum downstream bandwidth, in bits per second, allowed for a service with this service class. Zero if there is no restriction of downstream bandwidth.

cwdIfQosProfMaxTxBurst.name: cwdIfQosProfMaxTxBurst
cwdIfQosProfMaxTxBurst.description: The maximum number of mini-slots that may be requested for a single upstream transmission. A value of zero means there is no limit.

cwdIfQosProfBaselinePrivacy.name: cwdIfQosProfBaselinePrivacy
cwdIfQosProfBaselinePrivacy.description: Indicates whether Baseline Privacy is enabled for this service class.

cwdIfQosProfStatus.name: cwdIfQosProfStatus
cwdIfQosProfStatus.description: Controls and reflects the status of rows in this table.

cwdIfSignalQualityTable.name: cwdIfSignalQualityTable
cwdIfSignalQualityTable.description: At the SU, this table describes the PHY signal quality of downstream channels. At the HE, this table describes the PHY signal quality of upstream channels.

cwdIfSignalQualityEntry.name: cwdIfSignalQualityEntry
cwdIfSignalQualityEntry.description: At the SU, describes the PHY signal quality of a downstream channel. At the HE, describes the PHY signal quality of an upstream channel. An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of propDocsWirelessUpstream(nnn) for Head-End Systems and propDocsWirelessDownstream(nnn) for Subscriber units.

cwdIfSigQIncludesContention.name: cwdIfSigQIncludesContention
cwdIfSigQIncludesContention.description: true(1) if this HE includes contention intervals in the counters in this table. Always false(2) for SUs.

cwdIfSigQUnerroreds.name: cwdIfSigQUnerroreds
cwdIfSigQUnerroreds.description: Codewords received on this channel without error. This includes all codewords, whether or not they were part of frames destined for this device.

cwdIfSigQCorrecteds.name: cwdIfSigQCorrecteds
cwdIfSigQCorrecteds.description: Codewords received on this channel with correctable errors. This includes all codewords, whether or not they were part of frames destined for this device.

cwdIfSigQUncorrectables.name: cwdIfSigQUncorrectables
cwdIfSigQUncorrectables.description: Codewords received on this channel with uncorrectable errors. This includes all codewords, whether or not they were part of frames destined for this device.

cwdIfSigQSignalNoise.name: cwdIfSigQSignalNoise
cwdIfSigQSignalNoise.description: Signal to Interference plus Noise ratio as perceived for this channel.

cwdIfModulationTable.name: cwdIfModulationTable
cwdIfModulationTable.description: Describes modulation parameters associated with one or more upstream and/or downstream channels.

cwdIfModulationEntry.name: cwdIfModulationEntry
cwdIfModulationEntry.description: Describes a modulation profile for one or more upstream and downstream channels. Initial default entries may be created at system initialization time by the agent. The row operation for this table is as follows : 1. Any arbitrary index within the range can be used to create a row. 2. No individual non-index objects have to be specified in order to create an entry in this table. 3. CreateAndWait is not supported. 4. You can update/change the values in a row when the row is active. 5. The rows can be destroyed any time.

cwdIfModIndex.name: cwdIfModIndex
cwdIfModIndex.description: An index into the Channel Modulation table (cwdIfModulationTable) representing modulation parameters of a channel.

cwdIfModRowStatus.name: cwdIfModRowStatus
cwdIfModRowStatus.description: Controls and reflects the status of rows in this table.

cwdIfModBandwidth.name: cwdIfModBandwidth
cwdIfModBandwidth.description: The maximum bandwidth that can be used by a channel with using this modulation profile.

cwdIfModThroughput.name: cwdIfModThroughput
cwdIfModThroughput.description: This represents the throughput expected of the identified radio link.

cwdIfModBurstLength.name: cwdIfModBurstLength
cwdIfModBurstLength.description: The duration of the OFDM burst used by the physical layer. This is also the duration of the MAC minislot. Not all the settings will be supported by a particular ODU. Consult the capabilities of the ODU to determine the best burst length setting to use. The exact durations are hardware and implementation dependent.

cwdIfModMultipathRobustness.name: cwdIfModMultipathRobustness
cwdIfModMultipathRobustness.description: The quantitative level of robustness to multipath (also known as delay spread tolerance). The degree of multipath in the environment will vary with deployment. Consult installation and deployment documentation to determine the best setting to use.

cwdIfSuMacTable.name: cwdIfSuMacTable
cwdIfSuMacTable.description: Describes the attributes of each SU MAC interface, extending the information available from ifEntry.

cwdIfSuMacEntry.name: cwdIfSuMacEntry
cwdIfSuMacEntry.description: An entry containing objects describing attributes of each MAC entry, extending the information in ifEntry. An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of propDocsWirelessMacLayer(nnn).

cwdIfSuHeAddress.name: cwdIfSuHeAddress
cwdIfSuHeAddress.description: Identifies the HE that controls this MAC domain. At the SU, this will be the source address from SYNC, MAP, and other MAC-layer messages. If the HE is unknown, returns 00-00-00-00-00-00.

cwdIfSuCapabilities.name: cwdIfSuCapabilities
cwdIfSuCapabilities.description: Identifies the capabilities of the MAC implementation at this interface. Note that packet transmission is always supported. Therefore, there is no specific bit required to explicitly indicate this capability.

cwdIfSuRangingRespTimeout.name: cwdIfSuRangingRespTimeout
cwdIfSuRangingRespTimeout.reference: Data over Cable Radio Frequency Interface specification, Section 7, timer T3
cwdIfSuRangingRespTimeout.description: Waiting time for a Ranging Response packet.

cwdIfSuStatusTable.name: cwdIfSuStatusTable
cwdIfSuStatusTable.description: This table maintains a number of status objects and counters for Subscriber Units.

cwdIfSuStatusEntry.name: cwdIfSuStatusEntry
cwdIfSuStatusEntry.description: A set of status objects and counters for a single MAC layer instance in a Subscriber unit. An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of propDocsWirelessMacLayer(nnn).

cwdIfSuStatusValue.name: cwdIfSuStatusValue
cwdIfSuStatusValue.reference: Data over Cable Radio Frequency Interface Specification, Chapter 7.2.
cwdIfSuStatusValue.description: Current Subscriber unit connectivity state, as specified in the RF Interface Specification.

cwdIfSuStatusCode.name: cwdIfSuStatusCode
cwdIfSuStatusCode.reference: Data over Cable Radio Frequency Interface Specification, Subscriber unit status codes.
cwdIfSuStatusCode.description: Status code for this Subscriber unit as defined in the RF Interface Specification. The status code consists of a single character indicating error groups, followed by a two- or three-digit number indicating the status condition.

cwdIfSuStatusTxPower.name: cwdIfSuStatusTxPower
cwdIfSuStatusTxPower.description: The operational transmit power for the attached upstream channel.

cwdIfSuStatusResets.name: cwdIfSuStatusResets
cwdIfSuStatusResets.description: Number of times the SU reset or initialized this interface.

cwdIfSuStatusLostSyncs.name: cwdIfSuStatusLostSyncs
cwdIfSuStatusLostSyncs.description: Number of times the SU lost synchronization with the downstream channel.

cwdIfSuStatusInvalidMaps.name: cwdIfSuStatusInvalidMaps
cwdIfSuStatusInvalidMaps.description: Number of times the SU received invalid MAP messages.

cwdIfSuStatusInvalidUcds.name: cwdIfSuStatusInvalidUcds
cwdIfSuStatusInvalidUcds.description: Number of times the SU received invalid UCD messages.

cwdIfSuStatusInvalidRangingResp.name: cwdIfSuStatusInvalidRangingResp
cwdIfSuStatusInvalidRangingResp.description: Number of times the SU received invalid ranging response messages.

cwdIfSuStatusInvalidRegResp.name: cwdIfSuStatusInvalidRegResp
cwdIfSuStatusInvalidRegResp.description: Number of times the SU received invalid registration response messages.

cwdIfSuStatusT1Timeouts.name: cwdIfSuStatusT1Timeouts
cwdIfSuStatusT1Timeouts.description: Number of times counter T1 expired in the SU.

cwdIfSuStatusT2Timeouts.name: cwdIfSuStatusT2Timeouts
cwdIfSuStatusT2Timeouts.description: Number of times counter T2 expired in the SU.

cwdIfSuStatusT3Timeouts.name: cwdIfSuStatusT3Timeouts
cwdIfSuStatusT3Timeouts.description: Number of times counter T3 expired in the SU.

cwdIfSuStatusT4Timeouts.name: cwdIfSuStatusT4Timeouts
cwdIfSuStatusT4Timeouts.description: Number of times counter T4 expired in the SU.

cwdIfSuStatusRangingAborteds.name: cwdIfSuStatusRangingAborteds
cwdIfSuStatusRangingAborteds.description: Number of times the ranging process was aborted by the HE.

cwdIfSuServiceTable.name: cwdIfSuServiceTable
cwdIfSuServiceTable.description: Describes the attributes of each upstream service queue on a SU.

cwdIfSuServiceEntry.name: cwdIfSuServiceEntry
cwdIfSuServiceEntry.description: Describes the attributes of an upstream bandwidth service queue. An entry in this table exists for each Service ID. The primary index is an ifIndex with an ifType of propDocsWirelessMacLayer(nnn).

cwdIfSuServiceId.name: cwdIfSuServiceId
cwdIfSuServiceId.description: Identifies a service queue for upstream bandwidth. The attributes of this service queue are shared between the SU and the HE. The HE allocates upstream bandwidth to this service queue based on requests from the SU and on the class of service associated with this queue.

cwdIfSuServiceQosProfile.name: cwdIfSuServiceQosProfile
cwdIfSuServiceQosProfile.description: The index in cwdIfQosProfileTable describing the quality of service attributes associated with this particular service. If cwdIfQosProfileTable is not supported or doesn't exist, this object returns the value of zero.

cwdIfSuServiceTxSlotsImmed.name: cwdIfSuServiceTxSlotsImmed
cwdIfSuServiceTxSlotsImmed.description: The number of upstream mini-slots which have been used to transmit data PDUs in immediate (contention) mode. This includes only those PDUs which are presumed to have arrived at the headend (i.e., those which were explicitly acknowledged.) It does not include retransmission attempts or mini-slots used by requests.

cwdIfSuServiceTxSlotsDed.name: cwdIfSuServiceTxSlotsDed
cwdIfSuServiceTxSlotsDed.description: The number of upstream mini-slots which have been used to transmit data PDUs in dedicated mode (i.e., as a result of a unicast Data Grant).

cwdIfSuServiceTxRetries.name: cwdIfSuServiceTxRetries
cwdIfSuServiceTxRetries.description: The data PDUs transmitted directly in contention data slots expects explicit acknowledgement from the Headend. If the acknowledgement is not received the PDUs are transmitted again. This object is the number of attempts to transmit data PDUs which didn't receive acknowledgement.

cwdIfSuServiceTxExceeded.name: cwdIfSuServiceTxExceeded
cwdIfSuServiceTxExceeded.description: The data PDUs transmitted directly in contention data slots expects explicit acknowledgement from the Headend. If the acknowledgement is not received the PDUs are transmitted again. After excessive retries the data PDUs are dropped. This object represents the number of data PDU transmission failures due to excessive retries without acknowledgment.

cwdIfSuServiceRqRetries.name: cwdIfSuServiceRqRetries
cwdIfSuServiceRqRetries.description: The number of attempts to transmit bandwidth requests which did not result in acknowledgment.

cwdIfSuServiceRqExceeded.name: cwdIfSuServiceRqExceeded
cwdIfSuServiceRqExceeded.description: The number of requests for bandwidth which failed due to excessive retries without acknowledgment.

cwdIfHeMacTable.name: cwdIfHeMacTable
cwdIfHeMacTable.description: Describes the attributes of each HE MAC interface, extending the information available from ifEntry.

cwdIfHeMacEntry.name: cwdIfHeMacEntry
cwdIfHeMacEntry.description: An entry containing objects describing attributes of each MAC entry, extending the information in ifEntry. An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of propDocsWirelessMacLayer(nnn).

cwdIfHeCapabilities.name: cwdIfHeCapabilities
cwdIfHeCapabilities.description: Identifies the capabilities of the HE MAC implementation at this interface. Note that packet transmission is always supported. Therefore, there is no specific bit required to explicitly indicate this capability.

cwdIfHeSyncInterval.name: cwdIfHeSyncInterval
cwdIfHeSyncInterval.reference: Data Over Cable Radio Frequency Interface Specification, Sync Interval.
cwdIfHeSyncInterval.description: The interval between HE transmission of successive SYNC messages at this interface.

cwdIfHeUcdInterval.name: cwdIfHeUcdInterval
cwdIfHeUcdInterval.reference: Data Over Cable Radio Frequency Interface Specification, UCD Interval.
cwdIfHeUcdInterval.description: The interval between HE transmission of successive Upstream Channel Descriptor messages for each upstream channel at this interface.

cwdIfHeMaxServiceIds.name: cwdIfHeMaxServiceIds
cwdIfHeMaxServiceIds.reference: Data Over Cable Radio Frequency Interface Specification, Appendix A. Well-Known Addresses. A.2 MAC Service IDs.
cwdIfHeMaxServiceIds.description: The maximum number of service IDs that may be simultaneously active.

cwdIfHeInsertionInterval.name: cwdIfHeInsertionInterval
cwdIfHeInsertionInterval.reference: Data Over Cable Radio Frequency Interface Specification, Ranging Interval.
cwdIfHeInsertionInterval.description: The amount of time between each broadcast station maintenance grant. Broadcast station maintenance grants are used to allow new subscriber units to join the network. Zero indicates that a vendor-specific algorithm is used instead of a fixed time. Maximum amount of time permitted by the DOCSIS specification is 2 seconds.

cwdIfHeInvitedRangingAttempts.name: cwdIfHeInvitedRangingAttempts
cwdIfHeInvitedRangingAttempts.description: The maximum number of attempts to make on invitations for ranging requests. A value of zero means the system should attempt to range forever.

cwdIfHeStatusTable.name: cwdIfHeStatusTable
cwdIfHeStatusTable.description: For the MAC layer, this group maintains a number of status objects and counters.

cwdIfHeStatusEntry.name: cwdIfHeStatusEntry
cwdIfHeStatusEntry.description: Status entry for a single MAC layer. An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of propDocsWirelessMacLayer(nnn).

cwdIfHeStatusInvalidRangeReqs.name: cwdIfHeStatusInvalidRangeReqs
cwdIfHeStatusInvalidRangeReqs.description: This object counts invalid RNG-REQ messages received on this interface.

cwdIfHeStatusRangingAborteds.name: cwdIfHeStatusRangingAborteds
cwdIfHeStatusRangingAborteds.description: This object counts ranging attempts that were explicitly aborted by the HE.

cwdIfHeStatusInvalidRegReqs.name: cwdIfHeStatusInvalidRegReqs
cwdIfHeStatusInvalidRegReqs.description: This object counts invalid REG-REQ messages received on this interface.

cwdIfHeStatusFailedRegReqs.name: cwdIfHeStatusFailedRegReqs
cwdIfHeStatusFailedRegReqs.description: This object counts failed registration attempts, i.e., authentication failures and class of service failures, on this interface.

cwdIfHeStatusInvalidDataReqs.name: cwdIfHeStatusInvalidDataReqs
cwdIfHeStatusInvalidDataReqs.description: This object counts invalid data request messages received on this interface.

cwdIfHeStatusT5Timeouts.name: cwdIfHeStatusT5Timeouts
cwdIfHeStatusT5Timeouts.reference: Data Over Cable Radio Frequency Interface Specification, Sync Interval. Appendix B
cwdIfHeStatusT5Timeouts.description: This object counts the number of times counter T5 expired on this interface. The T5 timer is the 'Wait for Upstream Channel Change Response Timer' on the Head end.

cwdIfHeSuStatusTable.name: cwdIfHeSuStatusTable
cwdIfHeSuStatusTable.description: A set of objects in the HE, maintained for each Subscriber unit connected to this HE.

cwdIfHeSuStatusEntry.name: cwdIfHeSuStatusEntry
cwdIfHeSuStatusEntry.description: Status information for a single Subscriber unit. An entry in this table exists for each Subscriber unit that is connected to the HE implementing this table.

cwdIfHeSuStatusIndex.name: cwdIfHeSuStatusIndex
cwdIfHeSuStatusIndex.description: Index value to uniquely identify an entry in this table. For an individual Subscriber Unit, this index value should not change during HE uptime.

cwdIfHeSuStatusMacAddress.name: cwdIfHeSuStatusMacAddress
cwdIfHeSuStatusMacAddress.description: MAC address of this Subscriber Unit. If the Subscriber Unit has multiple MAC addresses, this is the MAC address associated with the Wireless interface. Each SU has only one wireless MAC interface.

cwdIfHeSuStatusIpAddress.name: cwdIfHeSuStatusIpAddress
cwdIfHeSuStatusIpAddress.description: IP address of this Subscriber Unit. If the Subscriber Unit has no IP address assigned, or the IP address is unknown, this object returns a value of 0.0.0.0. If the Subscriber Unit has multiple IP addresses, this object returns the IP address associated with the Wireless interface. Each SU has only one wireless MAC interface.

cwdIfHeSuStatusDownChanIfIndex.name: cwdIfHeSuStatusDownChanIfIndex
cwdIfHeSuStatusDownChanIfIndex.description: IfIndex of the downstream channel this Subscriber Unit is connected to. If the downstream channel is unknown, this object returns a value of zero.

cwdIfHeSuStatusUpChanIfIndex.name: cwdIfHeSuStatusUpChanIfIndex
cwdIfHeSuStatusUpChanIfIndex.description: IfIndex of the upstream channel this Subscriber Unit is connected to. If the upstream channel is unknown, this object returns a value of zero.

cwdIfHeSuStatusRxPower.name: cwdIfHeSuStatusRxPower
cwdIfHeSuStatusRxPower.description: The receive power as perceived for upstream data from this subscriber unit. If the receive power is unknown, this object returns a value of zero.

cwdIfHeSuStatusTimingOffset.name: cwdIfHeSuStatusTimingOffset
cwdIfHeSuStatusTimingOffset.description: A measure of the current round trip time for this SU. Used for timing of SU upstream transmissions to ensure synchronized arrivals at the HE. Units are in terms of (cwdIfUpstreamMiniSlotTimeBaseTick/64). Returns zero if the value is unknown.

cwdIfHeSuStatusValue.name: cwdIfHeSuStatusValue
cwdIfHeSuStatusValue.reference: Data over Cable Radio Frequency Interface Specification, Chapter 7.2.
cwdIfHeSuStatusValue.description: Current subscriber unit connectivity state, as specified in the RF Interface Specification. Returned status information is the SU status as assumed by the HE, and indicates the following events: other(1) Any state other than below. ranging(2) The HE has received an Initial Ranging Request message from the SU, and the ranging process is not yet complete. rangingAborted(3) The HE has sent a Ranging Abort message to the SU. rangingComplete(4) The HE has sent a Ranging Complete message to the SU. ipComplete(5) The HE has received a DHCP reply message and forwarded it to the SU. registrationComplete(6) The HE has sent a Registration Response message to the SU. accessDenied(7) The HE has sent a Registration Aborted message to the SU. The HE only needs to report states it is able to detect.

cwdIfHeSuStatusIfIndex.name: cwdIfHeSuStatusIfIndex
cwdIfHeSuStatusIfIndex.description: The HE MAC interface index (ifType of propDocsWirelessMacLayer(nnn)) that SU connects to.

cwdIfHeServiceTable.name: cwdIfHeServiceTable
cwdIfHeServiceTable.description: Describes the attributes of upstream service queues in a Head-end System.

cwdIfHeServiceEntry.name: cwdIfHeServiceEntry
cwdIfHeServiceEntry.description: Describes the attributes of a single upstream bandwidth service queue. Entries in this table exist for each ifEntry with an ifType of propDocsWirelessMacLayer(nnn), and for each service queue (Service ID) within this MAC layer. Entries in this table are created with the creation of individual Service IDs by the MAC layer and removed when a Service ID is removed.

cwdIfHeServiceId.name: cwdIfHeServiceId
cwdIfHeServiceId.description: Identifies a service queue for upstream bandwidth. The attributes of this service queue are shared between the Subscriber unit and the Head-end System. The HE allocates upstream bandwidth to this service queue based on requests from the SU and on the class of service associated with this queue.

cwdIfHeServiceSuStatusIndex.name: cwdIfHeServiceSuStatusIndex
cwdIfHeServiceSuStatusIndex.description: Pointer to an entry in cwdIfHeSuStatusTable identifying the Subscriber unit using this Service Queue.

cwdIfHeServiceAdminStatus.name: cwdIfHeServiceAdminStatus
cwdIfHeServiceAdminStatus.description: Allows a service class for a particular modem to be suppressed, (re-)enabled, or deleted altogether.

cwdIfHeServiceQosProfile.name: cwdIfHeServiceQosProfile
cwdIfHeServiceQosProfile.description: The index in cwdIfQosProfileTable describing the quality of service attributes associated with this particular service. If cwdIfQosProfileTable is not supported, this object returns the value of zero.

cwdIfHeServiceCreateTime.name: cwdIfHeServiceCreateTime

cwdIfHeServiceInPackets.name: cwdIfHeServiceInPackets

cwdIfHeQosProfilePermissions.name: cwdIfHeQosProfilePermissions
cwdIfHeQosProfilePermissions.description: This object specifies permitted methods of creating entries in cwdIfQosProfileTable. CreateByManagement(0) is set if entries can be created using SNMP. UpdateByManagement(1) is set if updating entries using SNMP is permitted. CreateBySubscriberUnits(2) is set if entries can be created based on information in REG-REQ MAC messages received from Subscriber units. Information in this object is only applicable if cwdIfQosProfileTable is implemented as read-create. Otherwise, this object is implemented as read-only and returns CreateBySubscriberUnits(2). Either CreateByManagement(0) or CreateBySubscriberUnits(2) must be set when writing to this object. If this object has a value of createByManagement(2) the qos entries can be created and modified by the management. If this object has a value of UpdateByManagement(1) the qos entries can be updated my management irrespective of who created it. But the management cannot create new entry in the cwdIfQosProfileTable.
